# Chapter 1 Project: Create a Representation

<div style="background-color: #a6e3e8; border-radius: 40px; color: #000000; width: 95%; padding: 1px 20px 1px 20px;">

<p style="line-height: 1.5; margin-left: 10px; margin-right: 10px; margin-top: 5px; margin-bottom: 5px; font-size: 17px; ">Chapter 1 of the Data and Society unit concludes with students designing a structure to represent their perfect day using the binary representation systems. Students start by writing a short description of their perfect day and then review with a partner to identify the key pieces of information they think a computer could capture. Then as a class they decide how a punch card of bytes of information will be interpreted to represent their pieces of information. Finally, students will use the ASCII, binary number, and image formats to represent their perfect days and trade their punch cards to try and decode what the other student's perfect day is like. The project concludes with students reflecting on their encoding and decoding process.
</p></div>

